HEADWORD: Pedestrianism
<hw>Pe*des"tri*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act,
art, or practice of a pedestrian; walking or running; traveling or
racing on foot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

